{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":317,"text":"I'll tell you a little bit\nabout irrational behavior."},{"time":3000,"text":"Not yours, of course -- other people's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4905,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":6111,"text":"So after being at MIT for a few years,"},{"time":10000,"text":"I realized that writing academic papers\nis not that exciting."},{"time":14681,"text":"You know, I don't know\nhow many of those you read,"},{"time":17063,"text":"but it's not fun to read\nand often not fun to write --"},{"time":19622,"text":"even worse to write."},{"time":21000,"text":"So I decided to try and write\nsomething more fun."},{"time":24000,"text":"And I came up with an idea\nthat I would write a cookbook."},{"time":28811,"text":"And the title for my cookbook\nwas going to be,"},{"time":30987,"text":"\"Dining Without Crumbs:\nThe Art of Eating Over the Sink.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":33871,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35617,"text":"And it was going to be a look\nat life through the kitchen."},{"time":38546,"text":"I was quite excited about this."},{"time":40125,"text":"I was going to talk\na little bit about research,"},{"time":42418,"text":"a little bit about the kitchen."},{"time":43939,"text":"We do so much in the kitchen,\nI thought this would be interesting."},{"time":47082,"text":"I wrote a couple of chapters,\nand took it to MIT Press and they said,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":50998,"text":"\"Cute, but not for us.\nGo and find somebody else.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":54116,"text":"I tried other people,\nand everybody said the same thing,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57021,"text":"\"Cute. Not for us.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":59116,"text":"Until somebody said,"},{"time":62000,"text":"\"Look, if you're serious about this,"},{"time":63850,"text":"you have to write about your research\nfirst; you have to publish something,"},{"time":67405,"text":"then you'll get the opportunity\nto write something else."},{"time":70127,"text":"If you really want to do it,\nyou have to do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":72422,"text":"I said, \"I don't want to write\nabout my research."},{"time":74791,"text":"I do it all day long,"},{"time":76032,"text":"I want to write something\na bit more free, less constrained.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":79548,"text":"And this person\nwas very forceful and said,"},{"time":82000,"text":"\"Look, that's the only way\nyou'll ever do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":84600,"text":"So I said, \"Okay, if I have to do it --\""},{"time":86934,"text":"I had a sabbatical."},{"time":88117,"text":"I said, \"I'll write about my research,\nif there's no other way."},{"time":91100,"text":"And then I'll get to do my cookbook.\""},{"time":92926,"text":"So, I wrote a book on my research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96186,"text":"And it turned out to be\nquite fun in two ways."},{"time":98781,"text":"First of all, I enjoyed writing."},{"time":101329,"text":"But the more interesting thing\nwas that I started learning from people."},{"time":105107,"text":"It's a fantastic time to write,"},{"time":106716,"text":"because there's so much feedback\nyou can get from people."},{"time":109445,"text":"People write to me\nabout their personal experience,"},{"time":112000,"text":"and about their examples,\nand where they disagree,"},{"time":114358,"text":"and their nuances."},{"time":116000,"text":"And even being here --\nI mean, the last few days,"},{"time":118310,"text":"I've known heights of obsessive behavior"},{"time":121000,"text":"I never thought about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":124656,"text":"Which I think is just fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126572,"text":"I will tell you a little bit\nabout irrational behavior,"},{"time":129191,"text":"and I want to start by giving you\nsome examples of visual illusion"},{"time":132393,"text":"as a metaphor for rationality."},{"time":134350,"text":"So think about these two tables."},{"time":136192,"text":"And you must have seen this illusion."},{"time":138000,"text":"If I asked you what's longer, the vertical\nline on the table on the left,"},{"time":141845,"text":"or the horizontal line\non the table on the right,"},{"time":144662,"text":"which one seems longer?"},{"time":147000,"text":"Can anybody see anything\nbut the left one being longer?"},{"time":149999,"text":"No, right? It's impossible."},{"time":151870,"text":"But the nice thing about visual illusion\nis we can easily demonstrate mistakes."},{"time":155786,"text":"So I can put some lines\non; it doesn't help."},{"time":158273,"text":"I can animate the lines."},{"time":159999,"text":"And to the extent you believe\nI didn't shrink the lines,"},{"time":162691,"text":"which I didn't, I've proven to you\nthat your eyes were deceiving you."},{"time":167503,"text":"Now, the interesting thing about this\nis when I take the lines away,"},{"time":171000,"text":"it's as if you haven't learned\nanything in the last minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173834,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176078,"text":"You can't look at this and say,\n\"Now I see reality as it is.\""},{"time":179793,"text":"Right? It's impossible to overcome\nthis sense that this is indeed longer."},{"time":183857,"text":"Our intuition is really fooling us"},{"time":185508,"text":"in a repeatable,\npredictable, consistent way."},{"time":187679,"text":"and there is almost nothing\nwe can do about it,"},{"time":190000,"text":"aside from taking a ruler\nand starting to measure it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193610,"text":"Here's another one.\nIt's one of my favorite illusions."},{"time":196198,"text":"What color is the top arrow pointing to?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199959,"text":"Audience: Brown.\nDan Ariely: Brown. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202155,"text":"The bottom one? Yellow."},{"time":204148,"text":"Turns out they're identical."},{"time":205513,"text":"Can anybody see them as identical?"},{"time":207448,"text":"Very, very hard."},{"time":208846,"text":"I can cover the rest of the cube up."},{"time":211000,"text":"If I cover the rest of the cube,\nyou can see that they are identical."},{"time":214430,"text":"If you don't believe me,\nyou can get the slide later"},{"time":216891,"text":"and do some arts and crafts\nand see that they're identical."},{"time":219731,"text":"But again, it's the same story,\nthat if we take the background away,"},{"time":223088,"text":"the illusion comes back."},{"time":225317,"text":"There is no way for us not\nto see this illusion."},{"time":228318,"text":"I guess maybe if you're colorblind,\nI don't think you can see that."},{"time":231659,"text":"I want you to think\nabout illusion as a metaphor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"Vision is one of the best things we do."},{"time":236159,"text":"We have a huge part of our brain\ndedicated to vision --"},{"time":238779,"text":"bigger than dedicated to anything else."},{"time":240698,"text":"We use our vision more hours\nof the day than anything else."},{"time":244570,"text":"We're evolutionarily\ndesigned to use vision."},{"time":246664,"text":"And if we have these predictable\nrepeatable mistakes in vision,"},{"time":249664,"text":"which we're so good at,"},{"time":251194,"text":"what are the chances we won't make\neven more mistakes"},{"time":253782,"text":"in something we're not as good at,\nfor example, financial decision-making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257357,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"Something we don't have\nan evolutionary reason to do,"},{"time":261674,"text":"we don't have a specialized\npart of the brain for,"},{"time":264048,"text":"and we don't do that many\nhours of the day."},{"time":266087,"text":"The argument is in those cases,"},{"time":268079,"text":"it might be that we actually\nmake many more mistakes."},{"time":272000,"text":"And worse -- not having\nan easy way to see them,"},{"time":274797,"text":"because in visual illusions, we can\neasily demonstrate the mistakes;"},{"time":278050,"text":"in cognitive illusion\nit's much, much harder"},{"time":280161,"text":"to demonstrate the mistakes to people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"So I want to show you\nsome cognitive illusions,"},{"time":285000,"text":"or decision-making illusions,\nin the same way."},{"time":288106,"text":"And this is one of my favorite\nplots in social sciences."},{"time":291606,"text":"It's from a paper\nby Johnson and Goldstein."},{"time":295468,"text":"It basically shows the percentage\nof people who indicated"},{"time":299190,"text":"they would be interested\nin donating their organs."},{"time":302944,"text":"These are different countries in Europe."},{"time":304893,"text":"You basically see two types of countries:"},{"time":306878,"text":"countries on the right,\nthat seem to be giving a lot;"},{"time":309504,"text":"and countries on the left\nthat seem to giving very little,"},{"time":312487,"text":"or much less."},{"time":314114,"text":"The question is, why?"},{"time":315290,"text":"Why do some countries give a lot\nand some countries give a little?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":318638,"text":"When you ask people this question,"},{"time":320290,"text":"they usually think that it has\nto be about culture."},{"time":322846,"text":"How much do you care about people?"},{"time":324496,"text":"Giving organs to somebody else"},{"time":326000,"text":"is probably about how much you care\nabout society, how linked you are."},{"time":329358,"text":"Or maybe it's about religion."},{"time":331000,"text":"But if you look at this plot,"},{"time":332979,"text":"you can see that countries\nthat we think about as very similar,"},{"time":336430,"text":"actually exhibit very different behavior."},{"time":339208,"text":"For example, Sweden\nis all the way on the right,"},{"time":341493,"text":"and Denmark, which we think\nis culturally very similar,"},{"time":344176,"text":"is all the way on the left."},{"time":346000,"text":"Germany is on the left,\nand Austria is on the right."},{"time":350000,"text":"The Netherlands is on the left,\nand Belgium is on the right."},{"time":353340,"text":"And finally, depending\non your particular version"},{"time":356000,"text":"of European similarity,"},{"time":358000,"text":"you can think about the U.K. and France\nas either similar culturally or not,"},{"time":363190,"text":"but it turns out that with organ\ndonation, they are very different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367038,"text":"By the way, the Netherlands\nis an interesting story."},{"time":369501,"text":"You see, the Netherlands is kind\nof the biggest of the small group."},{"time":374334,"text":"It turns out that they got to 28 percent"},{"time":377000,"text":"after mailing every household\nin the country a letter,"},{"time":380303,"text":"begging people to join\nthis organ donation program."},{"time":383512,"text":"You know the expression,\n\"Begging only gets you so far.\""},{"time":386504,"text":"It's 28 percent in organ donation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391273,"text":"But whatever the countries\non the right are doing,"},{"time":393647,"text":"they're doing a much\nbetter job than begging."},{"time":395782,"text":"So what are they doing?"},{"time":397114,"text":"Turns out the secret has to do\nwith a form at the DMV."},{"time":400606,"text":"And here is the story."},{"time":402000,"text":"The countries on the left\nhave a form at the DMV"},{"time":404531,"text":"that looks something like this."},{"time":406246,"text":"\"Check the box below if you want to\nparticipate in the organ donor program.\""},{"time":410555,"text":"And what happens?"},{"time":412000,"text":"People don't check, and they don't join."},{"time":415000,"text":"The countries on the right,\nthe ones that give a lot,"},{"time":417526,"text":"have a slightly different form."},{"time":419152,"text":"It says, \"Check the box below\nif you don't want to participate ...\""},{"time":422676,"text":"Interestingly enough,\nwhen people get this,"},{"time":424890,"text":"they again don't check, but now they join."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"Now, think about what this means."},{"time":433406,"text":"You know, we wake up in the morning\nand we feel we make decisions."},{"time":437000,"text":"We wake up in the morning\nand we open the closet;"},{"time":439334,"text":"we feel that we decide what to wear."},{"time":441142,"text":"we open the refrigerator and we feel\nthat we decide what to eat."},{"time":444238,"text":"What this is actually saying,"},{"time":445761,"text":"is that many of these decisions\nare not residing within us."},{"time":448595,"text":"They are residing in the person\nwho is designing that form."},{"time":451721,"text":"When you walk into the DMV,"},{"time":453691,"text":"the person who designed the form\nwill have a huge influence"},{"time":456714,"text":"on what you'll end up doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458547,"text":"Now, it's also very hard\nto intuit these results."},{"time":461350,"text":"Think about it for yourself."},{"time":462715,"text":"How many of you believe"},{"time":464000,"text":"that if you went to renew\nyour license tomorrow,"},{"time":466310,"text":"and you went to the DMV,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and you encountered one of these forms,"},{"time":470291,"text":"that it would actually\nchange your own behavior?"},{"time":472776,"text":"Very hard to think\nthat it would influence us."},{"time":475107,"text":"We can say, \"Oh, these funny Europeans,\nof course it would influence them.\""},{"time":478670,"text":"But when it comes to us,"},{"time":480457,"text":"we have such a feeling\nthat we're in the driver's seat,"},{"time":483119,"text":"such a feeling that we're in control\nand we are making the decision,"},{"time":486432,"text":"that it's very hard\nto even accept the idea"},{"time":489055,"text":"that we actually have an illusion\nof making a decision,"},{"time":491754,"text":"rather than an actual decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493842,"text":"Now, you might say,"},{"time":496334,"text":"\"These are decisions we don't care about.\""},{"time":498775,"text":"In fact, by definition,\nthese are decisions"},{"time":501072,"text":"about something that will happen\nto us after we die."},{"time":503679,"text":"How could we care about something less"},{"time":505823,"text":"than about something\nthat happens after we die?"},{"time":508136,"text":"So a standard economist,\nsomebody who believes in rationality,"},{"time":511082,"text":"would say, \"You know what?"},{"time":512359,"text":"The cost of lifting the pencil\nand marking a \"V\" is higher"},{"time":515835,"text":"than the possible benefit of the decision,"},{"time":518000,"text":"so that's why we get this effect.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":519822,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520855,"text":"But, in fact, it's not because it's easy."},{"time":523377,"text":"It's not because it's trivial.\nIt's not because we don't care."},{"time":526417,"text":"It's the opposite. It's because we care."},{"time":528862,"text":"It's difficult and it's complex."},{"time":530830,"text":"And it's so complex\nthat we don't know what to do."},{"time":533405,"text":"And because we have no idea what to do,"},{"time":535405,"text":"we just pick whatever it was\nthat was chosen for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539609,"text":"I'll give you one more example."},{"time":541174,"text":"This is from a paper\nby Redelmeier and Shafir."},{"time":543785,"text":"And they said, \"Would this\neffect also happens to experts?"},{"time":547315,"text":"People who are well-paid,\nexperts in their decisions,"},{"time":550467,"text":"and who make a lot of them?\""},{"time":551847,"text":"And they took a group of physicians."},{"time":554056,"text":"They presented to them\na case study of a patient."},{"time":556532,"text":"They said, \"Here is a patient.\nHe is a 67-year-old farmer."},{"time":560000,"text":"He's been suffering from\nright hip pain for a while.\""},{"time":562754,"text":"And then, they said to the physicians,"},{"time":564612,"text":"\"You decided a few weeks ago"},{"time":566000,"text":"that nothing is working for this patient."},{"time":568000,"text":"All these medications,\nnothing seems to be working."},{"time":570453,"text":"So you refer the patient\nfor hip replacement therapy."},{"time":573249,"text":"Hip replacement. Okay?\""},{"time":575000,"text":"So the patient is on a path\nto have his hip replaced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578456,"text":"Then they said to half of the physicians,"},{"time":580449,"text":"\"Yesterday, you reviewed\nthe patient's case,"},{"time":582812,"text":"and you realized that you forgot\nto try one medication."},{"time":585446,"text":"You did not try ibuprofen."},{"time":588000,"text":"What do you do? Do you pull\nthe patient back and try ibuprofen?"},{"time":591349,"text":"Or do you let him go\nand have hip replacement?\""},{"time":594143,"text":"Well, the good news is\nthat most physicians in this case"},{"time":596818,"text":"decided to pull the patient\nand try ibuprofen."},{"time":599651,"text":"Very good for the physicians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601415,"text":"To the other group\nof physicians, they said,"},{"time":603506,"text":"\"Yesterday when you reviewed the case,\nyou discovered there were two medications"},{"time":607379,"text":"you didn't try out yet --\nibuprofen and piroxicam.\""},{"time":609919,"text":"You have two medications\nyou didn't try out yet."},{"time":612194,"text":"What do you do? You let him go,\nor you pull him back?"},{"time":614861,"text":"And if you pull him back, do you try\nibuprofen or piroxicam? Which one?\""},{"time":618329,"text":"Now, think of it:"},{"time":619509,"text":"This decision makes it as easy to let\nthe patient continue with hip replacement,"},{"time":623405,"text":"but pulling him back, all of the sudden\nit becomes more complex."},{"time":626555,"text":"There is one more decision."},{"time":628397,"text":"What happens now?"},{"time":629747,"text":"The majority of the physicians\nnow choose to let the patient go"},{"time":633390,"text":"for a hip replacement."},{"time":634931,"text":"I hope this worries you, by the way --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":638257,"text":"when you go to see your physician."},{"time":640622,"text":"The thing is that\nno physician would ever say,"},{"time":643368,"text":"\"Piroxicam, ibuprofen, hip replacement.\nLet's go for hip replacement.\""},{"time":647185,"text":"But the moment you set this\nas the default,"},{"time":650000,"text":"it has a huge power over whatever\npeople end up doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654000,"text":"I'll give you a couple of more examples\non irrational decision-making."},{"time":657358,"text":"Imagine I give you a choice:"},{"time":659200,"text":"Do you want to go for a weekend to Rome,\nall expenses paid --"},{"time":662837,"text":"hotel, transportation, food,\na continental breakfast, everything --"},{"time":667423,"text":"or a weekend in Paris?"},{"time":669000,"text":"Now, weekend in Paris, weekend\nin Rome -- these are different things."},{"time":672278,"text":"They have different food,\ndifferent culture, different art."},{"time":675080,"text":"Imagine I added a choice to the set\nthat nobody wanted."},{"time":678460,"text":"Imagine I said, \"A weekend in Rome,"},{"time":680236,"text":"a weekend in Paris,"},{"time":681628,"text":"or having your car stolen?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":683244,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":686301,"text":"It's a funny idea, because why\nwould having your car stolen,"},{"time":689571,"text":"in this set, influence anything?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691191,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":693329,"text":"But what if the option to have your car\nstolen was not exactly like this?"},{"time":697802,"text":"What if it was a trip to Rome,\nall expenses paid,"},{"time":700358,"text":"transportation, breakfast,"},{"time":702660,"text":"but it doesn't include\ncoffee in the morning?"},{"time":705000,"text":"If you want coffee, you have to pay\nfor it yourself, it's two euros 50."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708397,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":709428,"text":"Now in some ways,"},{"time":711000,"text":"given that you can have Rome with coffee,"},{"time":713323,"text":"why would you possibly\nwant Rome without coffee?"},{"time":715728,"text":"It's like having your car stolen.\nIt's an inferior option."},{"time":719314,"text":"But guess what happened?"},{"time":720490,"text":"The moment you add Rome without coffee,"},{"time":722825,"text":"Rome with coffee becomes more popular,\nand people choose it."},{"time":726467,"text":"The fact that you have Rome without coffee"},{"time":729000,"text":"makes Rome with coffee look superior,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and not just to Rome without coffee --\neven superior to Paris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738101,"text":"Here are two examples of this principle."},{"time":740577,"text":"This was an ad in The Economist\na few years ago"},{"time":743253,"text":"that gave us three choices:"},{"time":745357,"text":"an online subscription for 59 dollars,"},{"time":748214,"text":"a print subscription for 125 dollars,"},{"time":751723,"text":"or you could get both for 125."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"Now I looked at this,\nand I called up The Economist,"},{"time":758609,"text":"and I tried to figure out\nwhat they were thinking."},{"time":761196,"text":"And they passed me from one person\nto another to another,"},{"time":764362,"text":"until eventually I got to the person\nwho was in charge of the website,"},{"time":768109,"text":"and I called them up, and they went\nto check what was going on."},{"time":771728,"text":"The next thing I know,\nthe ad is gone, no explanation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775599,"text":"So I decided to do the experiment"},{"time":777510,"text":"that I would have loved\nThe Economist to do with me."},{"time":780176,"text":"I took this and I gave it\nto 100 MIT students."},{"time":782599,"text":"I said, \"What would you choose?\""},{"time":784187,"text":"These are the market shares --\nmost people wanted the combo deal."},{"time":788197,"text":"Thankfully, nobody wanted\nthe dominant option."},{"time":790429,"text":"That means our students can read."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792093,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":793499,"text":"But now, if you have an option\nthat nobody wants,"},{"time":796412,"text":"you can take it off, right?"},{"time":798135,"text":"So I printed another version of this,"},{"time":800000,"text":"where I eliminated the middle option."},{"time":801841,"text":"I gave it to another 100 students.\nHere is what happened:"},{"time":805348,"text":"Now the most popular option\nbecame the least popular,"},{"time":808109,"text":"and the least popular\nbecame the most popular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811641,"text":"What was happening\nwas the option that was useless,"},{"time":815000,"text":"in the middle, was useless\nin the sense that nobody wanted it."},{"time":818875,"text":"But it wasn't useless in the sense\nthat it helped people figure out"},{"time":822065,"text":"what they wanted."},{"time":823240,"text":"In fact, relative\nto the option in the middle,"},{"time":826000,"text":"which was get only the print for 125,"},{"time":830523,"text":"the print and web for 125\nlooked like a fantastic deal."},{"time":834300,"text":"And as a consequence, people chose it."},{"time":836427,"text":"The general idea here, by the way,"},{"time":838078,"text":"is that we actually don't know\nour preferences that well."},{"time":840793,"text":"And because we don't know\nour preferences that well,"},{"time":843287,"text":"we're susceptible to all of these\ninfluences from the external forces:"},{"time":846600,"text":"the defaults, the particular options\nthat are presented to us, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850632,"text":"One more example of this."},{"time":852000,"text":"People believe that when we deal\nwith physical attraction,"},{"time":855381,"text":"we see somebody, and we know immediately\nwhether we like them or not,"},{"time":858668,"text":"if we're attracted or not."},{"time":860000,"text":"This is why we have\nthese four-minute dates."},{"time":862456,"text":"So I decided to do\nthis experiment with people."},{"time":865000,"text":"I'll show you images here, no real people,\nbut the experiment was with people."},{"time":869000,"text":"I showed some people a picture\nof Tom, and a picture of Jerry."},{"time":872000,"text":"and I said, \"Who do you want to date?"},{"time":874093,"text":"Tom or Jerry?\""},{"time":875592,"text":"But for half the people,\nI added an ugly version of Jerry."},{"time":878895,"text":"I took Photoshop and I made\nJerry slightly less attractive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885437,"text":"For the other people, I added\nan ugly version of Tom."},{"time":889000,"text":"And the question was,\nwill ugly Jerry and ugly Tom"},{"time":892000,"text":"help their respective,\nmore attractive brothers?"},{"time":895792,"text":"The answer was absolutely yes."},{"time":898045,"text":"When ugly Jerry was around,\nJerry was popular."},{"time":900215,"text":"When ugly Tom was around, Tom was popular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902379,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"This of course has two\nvery clear implications"},{"time":906536,"text":"for life in general."},{"time":909790,"text":"If you ever go bar-hopping,\nwho do you want to take with you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":913000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918753,"text":"You want a slightly uglier\nversion of yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922554,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"Similar, but slightly uglier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926261,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":927728,"text":"The second point, or course, is that\nif somebody invites you to bar hop,"},{"time":931521,"text":"you know what they think about you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933292,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":936000,"text":"Now you get it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":938306,"text":"What is the general point?"},{"time":940000,"text":"The general point is that,"},{"time":941282,"text":"when we think about economics, we have\nthis beautiful view of human nature."},{"time":945000,"text":"\"What a piece of work is a man!\nHow noble in reason!\""},{"time":947561,"text":"We have this view of ourselves, of others."},{"time":950163,"text":"The behavioral economics perspective\nis slightly less \"generous\" to people;"},{"time":955401,"text":"in fact, in medical terms,"},{"time":957524,"text":"that's our view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958740,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":963891,"text":"But there is a silver lining."},{"time":966000,"text":"The silver lining is, I think,"},{"time":967898,"text":"kind of the reason that behavioral\neconomics is interesting and exciting."},{"time":972000,"text":"Are we Superman, or are we Homer Simpson?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975286,"text":"When it comes to building\nthe physical world,"},{"time":978301,"text":"we kind of understand our limitations."},{"time":980357,"text":"We build steps."},{"time":981552,"text":"And we build these things\nthat not everybody can use, obviously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984719,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":986639,"text":"We understand our limitations,"},{"time":988210,"text":"and we build around them."},{"time":989884,"text":"But for some reason, when it comes\nto the mental world,"},{"time":992487,"text":"when we design things like healthcare\nand retirement and stock markets,"},{"time":995868,"text":"we somehow forget the idea\nthat we are limited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998240,"text":"I think that if we understood\nour cognitive limitations"},{"time":1001171,"text":"in the same way we understand\nour physical limitations,"},{"time":1003807,"text":"even though they don't stare us\nin the face the same way,"},{"time":1006641,"text":"we could design a better world,\nand that, I think,"},{"time":1009145,"text":"is the hope of this thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010562,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}